"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown repeated her third place in Paris, aged 16.\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2155, \"end\": 2160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.8825700713373036e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Harry Edward became Britain's first black Olympian at the 1920 Games in Antwerp, where he won bronze medals in both the 100m and 200m.\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2172, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Edward\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harry Edward\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Edward\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Edward\"}, {\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999989317985, \"rank\": 1.068189332703508e-09, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.999999936862425, \"rank\": 6.313771121002953e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2244, \"end\": 2251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"score\": 0.9965714441347586, \"rank\": 0.0034400803594891263, \"text\": \"Antwerp\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Berlin-born, with British nationality through his father from the then British colony of Dominica, 