 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Polytechnic Harriers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingston_Athletic_Club_and_Polytechnic_Harriers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingston_Athletic_Club_and_Polytechnic_Harriers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was later a humanitarian aid worker for the United Nations and the International Refugee Organisation.\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2672, \"end\": 2686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.9999540549206747, \"rank\": 3.849400629882542e-05, \"text\": \"United Nations\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}, {\"begin\": 2695, \"end\": 2729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Refugee_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Refugee Organisation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Refugee_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Refugee_Organization\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lutalo Muhammad missed out on a gold medal by a single second in a dramatic men's taekwondo final in Rio in 2016.\", \"from\": 2732, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2732, \"end\": 2747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lutalo_Muhammad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lutalo Muhammad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lutalo_Muhammad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lutalo_Muhammad\"}, {\"begin\": 2833, \"end\": 2836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.863031876466515e-18, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Muhammad held a one-point lead over Cheick Sallah Cisse of the Ivory Coast heading into the final stages of their final before his opponent landed a swinging head kick worth two points with just one second left on the clock.\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 3070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\", \"score\": 0.9999029422694061, \"rank\": 9.67112640427869e-05, \"text\": \"Muhammad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad\"}, {\"begin\": 2889, \"end\": 2895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sallah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sallah\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sallah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sallah\"}, {\"begin\": 2909, \"end\": 2920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\", \"score\": 0.9876757388182641, \"rank\": 0.012477936891543777, \"text\": \"Ivory Coast\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ivory_Coast\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ethel Muckelt, from Moss Side in Manchester, won Great Britain's first medal at a Winter Olympics when she took bronze in the women's figure skating at the inaugural Winter Games in Chamonix in 1924.\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3072, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethel_Muckelt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethel Muckelt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethel_Muckelt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethel_Muckelt\"}, {\"begin\": 3092, \"end\": 3101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moss_Side\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.604736588640957e-17, \"text\": \"Moss Side\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moss_Side\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moss_Side\"}, {\"begin\": 3121, \"end\": 3134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.551782753003843e-13, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3254, \"end\": 3262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1776845990538528e-36, \"text\": \"Chamonix\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Muckelt was not the first British figure skater to win an Olympic medal - GB won figure skating medals in both 1908 and 1924, when it was part of the summer programme.\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3302, \"end\": 3309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999777674022, \"rank\": 1.8125684117597205e-08, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Jenny Jones won a bronze medal in the women's snowboard slopestyle event at the 2014 Games in Sochi, she became the first British athlete to win a Winter Olympic medal on snow.\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3450, \"end\": 3461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Jenny_Jones_Show\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9833018115037503e-16, \"text\": \"Jenny Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Jenny_Jones_Show\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Jenny_Jones_Show\"}, {\"begin\": 3544, \"end\": 3549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999996481838643, \"rank\": 3.518160498583189e-07, \"text\": \"Sochi\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2014_Winter_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3572, \"end\": 3579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999999777674022, \"rank\": 1.8125684117597205e-08, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four years later, Izzy Atkin finished third in the women's ski slopestyle to become the first Briton to win an Olympic medal on skis.\", \"from\": 3627, \"to\": 3760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3645, \"end\": 3655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabel_Atkin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Izzy Atkin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabel_Atkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isabel_Atkin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two medals are missing from this list.\", \"from\": 3762, \"to\": 3800, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The silver won by the men's 4\\u00d7100 metres relay team in Tokyo, which was stripped after CJ Ujah failed a drugs test and the bronze won by Alain Baxter in the men's slalom at the 2002 Salt Lake City Winter Olympics, which was taken away after he tested positive for a banned substance contained in a nasal decongestant.\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 4118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3856, \"end\": 3861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9898486926526662, \"rank\": 0.01025541312265706, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 3888, \"end\": 3895, \"title\": \"http://dbpe